<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1325,284,1070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,426,964,990]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[433,462,964,990]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">—</emphasis>
The irregular shape of the parameres and the high and very sharp lobes of the aedeagus are peculiar to this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[312,1251,1044,1070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[264,1325,284,1070]" box="[312,1251,1044,1070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,445,1044,1070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Etymology</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[452,481,1044,1070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">—</emphasis>
The name refers to the very long and sharp lobes of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
